1
00:00:06,466 --> 00:00:09,166
(Previously)
No one treats you better than I do.

2
00:00:12,066 --> 00:00:13,300
Please be my boyfriend

3
00:00:21,900 --> 00:00:24,193
Let's go, Sis Chon.

4
00:00:24,194 --> 00:00:25,194
Okay, let's go.

5
00:00:33,666 --> 00:00:35,700
Hey, Nai. It's Ton.

6
00:00:35,800 --> 00:00:37,206
Yeah, I know it's you.

7
00:00:37,207 --> 00:00:39,003
Have you reached In's love nest yet?

8
00:00:39,004 --> 00:00:40,666
So, did you find out anything?

9
00:00:40,876 --> 00:00:42,887
Yeah, he actually calls that
little fierce his "beloved wife."

10
00:00:42,911 --> 00:00:44,714
And he looks at him with such dreamy eyes.

11
00:00:44,715 --> 00:00:48,166
And when they came downstairs just now, I
saw little fierce covered in hickeys from In.

12
00:00:48,300 --> 00:00:50,266
Holy crap. He must be under a spell.

13
00:00:50,700 --> 00:00:51,700
This is bad.

14
00:00:51,866 --> 00:00:53,942
Casanova In can't
lose his edge like this.

15
00:00:53,966 --> 00:00:55,442
We have to find a way to help our friend.

16
00:00:55,466 --> 00:00:56,266
How?

17
00:00:56,333 --> 00:00:57,166
By breaking the spell!

18
00:00:57,300 --> 00:00:58,755
We need to find a famous spiritual master.

19
00:00:58,756 --> 00:00:59,756
Huh?

20
00:01:00,133 --> 00:01:01,133
Where?

21
00:01:02,966 --> 00:01:04,866
But I don't really believe in black magic.

22
00:01:05,066 --> 00:01:06,366
In always tells me...

23
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:08,076
to respect things even
if I don't believe in them.

24
00:01:08,100 --> 00:01:09,133
We should ask In.

25
00:01:09,366 --> 00:01:10,646
He knows a lot about this stuff.

26
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:14,733
No, we can't just ask him. We need
to find an old master to break this spell.

27
00:01:14,866 --> 00:01:16,285
Damn, this is hard.

28
00:01:16,286 --> 00:01:17,534
I'm so worried about him.

29
00:01:17,535 --> 00:01:20,006
Tonhon, my friend, we
have to do something fast.

30
00:01:20,007 --> 00:01:23,800
I saw in a movie that people under spells
for too long will actually wither and die.

31
00:01:24,500 --> 00:01:27,139
Hey, should we consult Nai?

32
00:01:27,140 --> 00:01:30,380
Scientifically speaking, he might just be
obsessed with him because of pheromones.

33
00:01:30,733 --> 00:01:31,533
I just called him.

34
00:01:31,666 --> 00:01:33,133
He told us to mind our own business.

35
00:01:33,933 --> 00:01:35,133
Then I'll search Google.

36
00:01:35,166 --> 00:01:36,206
About how to break spells.

37
00:01:36,266 --> 00:01:37,266
I'll call you back.

38
00:01:37,366 --> 00:01:38,666
I think they're coming down.

39
00:01:38,766 --> 00:01:39,400
Yeah, yeah.

40
00:01:39,401 --> 00:01:40,700
Say hi to Chonlatee for me.

41
00:01:40,766 --> 00:01:41,400
Mwah!

42
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:42,400
Mind your own business.

43
00:01:48,266 --> 00:01:50,166
Sis, you can sit here first.

44
00:01:50,333 --> 00:01:51,666
Uh-huh, sure.

45
00:01:52,500 --> 00:01:54,894
I'm going to check the
things the workers brought in.

46
00:01:54,895 --> 00:01:56,055
To see if everything is here.

47
00:01:56,666 --> 00:01:58,800
Okay. Let me know if you need any help.

48
00:01:59,300 --> 00:02:00,300
I'm good, thank you.

49
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:02,908
What did you do upstairs?

50
00:02:02,933 --> 00:02:04,600
We were just chatting.

51
00:02:04,965 --> 00:02:05,670
Are you sure?

52
00:02:05,670 --> 00:02:06,670
Yes.

53
00:02:08,050 --> 00:02:09,500
Wow, you guys are amazing.

54
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:12,400
This is great. Please
take care of the front too.

55
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:15,766
There's still a lot more over there.

56
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:18,800
Here.

57
00:02:18,933 --> 00:02:20,066
Damn, He's so fierce.

58
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:23,000
Move everything, guys.

59
00:02:23,566 --> 00:02:24,566
Ton.

60
00:02:24,866 --> 00:02:25,666
Ton!

61
00:02:25,733 --> 00:02:26,233
Huh?

62
00:02:26,234 --> 00:02:27,333
Why the long face?

63
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:29,666
I was just on the phone with Ni.

64
00:02:29,733 --> 00:02:32,933
Ni and I are wondering
if In is under some kind of spell.

65
00:02:33,266 --> 00:02:33,816
What?

66
00:02:33,816 --> 00:02:34,816
Yeah.

67
00:02:35,508 --> 00:02:36,508
Why would you think that?

68
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:39,400
Just look at how obsessed In is with him.

69
00:02:40,500 --> 00:02:43,300
I don't think so. I think
they're sweet together.

70
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:46,676
I still don't see what's
so great about little fierce.

71
00:02:46,700 --> 00:02:48,427
I think he's actually quite cute.

72
00:02:48,452 --> 00:02:50,349
Especially when he
talks with all that attitude,

73
00:02:50,350 --> 00:02:51,733
and puts so much energy into it.

74
00:02:52,966 --> 00:02:53,966
How is that cute?

75
00:02:54,264 --> 00:02:55,620
I don't see any good
qualities in him at all.

76
00:02:55,621 --> 00:02:58,237
I should go talk to little fierce myself.

77
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:07,766
Do you have a problem with me?

78
00:03:08,166 --> 00:03:09,166
Yes, I do.

79
00:03:10,966 --> 00:03:12,006
I have a question for you.

80
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:13,100
About what?

81
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:14,890
You cast a spell on my friend, didn't you?

82
00:03:14,891 --> 00:03:15,891
A spell?

83
00:03:16,733 --> 00:03:17,973
You mean...

84
00:03:18,247 --> 00:03:19,900
like black magic or something?

85
00:03:20,066 --> 00:03:22,266
Yeah, like a love potion or a charm.

86
00:03:23,666 --> 00:03:24,666
I didn't do anything.

87
00:03:24,900 --> 00:03:25,533
You didn't?

88
00:03:25,534 --> 00:03:27,174
Then why is my friend so crazy about you?

89
00:03:28,766 --> 00:03:30,000
Because I really didn't do it.

90
00:03:30,333 --> 00:03:31,333
You did, didn't you?

91
00:03:31,366 --> 00:03:32,166
I didn't do it.

92
00:03:32,266 --> 00:03:33,666
Just tell me where you got it done.

93
00:03:33,700 --> 00:03:34,780
I told you, I didn't do it!

94
00:03:35,333 --> 00:03:37,400
Tell me right now where you got it!

95
00:03:37,700 --> 00:03:39,265
In case Chon stops loving me one day...

96
00:03:39,266 --> 00:03:40,933
so I can go get one too.

97
00:03:43,500 --> 00:03:44,917
Pee Ton, calm down.

98
00:03:44,918 --> 00:03:47,594
Calm down and repeat after me.

99
00:03:47,595 --> 00:03:48,595
Wait.

100
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:11,400
Repeat after me.

101
00:04:12,066 --> 00:04:13,200
[chanting spell]

102
00:04:14,100 --> 00:04:15,133
[chanting spell]

103
00:04:16,133 --> 00:04:17,133
You jerk.

104
00:04:17,637 --> 00:04:19,136
[chanting spell]

105
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:23,333
What the hell are you guys doing?

106
00:04:23,835 --> 00:04:25,705
[chanting spell]
expecto patronum

107
00:04:27,943 --> 00:04:29,943
Why did you buy chicken
noodles just for yourself?

108
00:04:31,308 --> 00:04:32,308
[chanting spell]

109
00:04:34,700 --> 00:04:36,140
But you ordered rolled rice noodles.

110
00:04:37,300 --> 00:04:38,866
I want some chicken noodles too.

111
00:04:40,266 --> 00:04:42,100
I'll share a chicken foot with you then.

112
00:04:44,866 --> 00:04:46,566
I'll go take care of it.

113
00:05:00,666 --> 00:05:03,600
I'm not surprised at all
why In is so crazy about little fierce.

114
00:05:04,533 --> 00:05:05,333
Uh...

115
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:08,066
They're actually a very
cute and lively couple.

116
00:05:08,933 --> 00:05:09,433
Really?

117
00:05:09,434 --> 00:05:10,700
They're quite sweet.

118
00:05:12,266 --> 00:05:14,266
No, they seem more like crazy people.

119
00:05:17,933 --> 00:05:18,933
The power is out.

120
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:22,700
Not cute?

121
00:05:23,266 --> 00:05:24,266
What is this?

122
00:05:33,566 --> 00:05:35,866
Why were you guys suddenly chanting spells?

123
00:05:36,133 --> 00:05:37,866
Go ask Ton.

124
00:05:38,900 --> 00:05:39,900
Dummy

125
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:41,733
What did you just call me?

126
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:44,200
Huh?

127
00:05:44,333 --> 00:05:45,333
I was going to say...

128
00:05:45,733 --> 00:05:46,733
honey.

129
00:05:49,900 --> 00:05:50,900
I heard you, you know.

130
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:54,600
Ton asked me
if I cast a spell on you.

131
00:05:55,066 --> 00:05:56,586
That's why you're so obsessed with me.

132
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:58,100
Really?

133
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:02,600
Oh!

134
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:03,800
Oh!

135
00:06:04,566 --> 00:06:05,566
This is so heavy.

136
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:08,800
Same old trick.

137
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:11,600
It would be nice if someone
helped me carry this.

138
00:06:23,066 --> 00:06:25,166
Why aren't you taking the hint today?

139
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:29,166
No, I want to see my wife
be a proper housewife for once.

140
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:33,900
Fine. Then I'm terminating our marriage
effective immediately.

141
00:06:36,133 --> 00:06:38,653
You lost that right the moment
you asked me to be your husband.

142
00:06:38,700 --> 00:06:39,940
I asked you to be my boyfriend.

143
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:41,200
Husband.

144
00:06:41,266 --> 00:06:41,766
Boyfriend.

145
00:06:41,767 --> 00:06:43,366
You asked me to be your husband.

146
00:06:43,533 --> 00:06:44,033
Got it?

147
00:06:44,033 --> 00:06:45,033
Boyfriend.

148
00:06:48,966 --> 00:06:49,966
I said Boyfriend!

149
00:06:50,066 --> 00:06:51,166
I said husband!

150
00:06:51,266 --> 00:06:52,100
Husband, husband, husband!

151
00:06:52,101 --> 00:06:53,799
Boyfriend, boyfriend, boyfriend!

152
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:54,900
I said husband.

153
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:56,040
- Boyfriend, boyfriend, boyfriend!
- Husband, husband, husband!

154
00:06:56,064 --> 00:06:58,544
- Boyfriend, boyfriend, boyfriend!
- Husband, husband, husband!

155
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:00,400
Husband.

156
00:07:01,133 --> 00:07:02,133
I'm leaving.

157
00:07:02,666 --> 00:07:03,666
You carry it yourself.

158
00:07:07,387 --> 00:07:08,387
Hey!

159
00:07:09,817 --> 00:07:10,817
Crazy husband.

160
00:07:58,700 --> 00:08:06,500
"ChermChey"
(Episode 5)

161
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,000
Dorky.

162
00:08:23,467 --> 00:08:24,657
Old-fashioned.

163
00:08:29,466 --> 00:08:30,466
So old-fashioned.

164
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,440
I really hate this shop sign.
(Chermchey, the name of the bar)

165
00:08:36,466 --> 00:08:37,905
Take a closer look, Erng.

166
00:08:38,910 --> 00:08:41,609
Our shop is the most
eye-catching one around here.

167
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,866
Yeah, I know.

168
00:08:50,466 --> 00:08:51,566
Is the lighting okay?

169
00:08:53,866 --> 00:08:54,866
I think so.

170
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:56,200
What do you think?

171
00:08:57,766 --> 00:08:58,766
Looks good.

172
00:09:04,300 --> 00:09:05,466
Let's go get some food.

173
00:09:06,333 --> 00:09:07,333
I'm getting hungry.

174
00:09:13,700 --> 00:09:14,700
Aren't you tired?

175
00:09:16,066 --> 00:09:17,933
Your hair is a mess from working so hard.

176
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:21,166
I told you before...

177
00:09:21,466 --> 00:09:22,466
that I'm a workaholic.

178
00:09:22,933 --> 00:09:24,400
You might have to deal with me...

179
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:26,820
forgetting my husband
because of work, like today.

180
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:29,100
But your husband didn't forget you.

181
00:09:30,266 --> 00:09:32,400
Whenever you're free,
I'll just come and bug you.

182
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:34,166
Besides...

183
00:09:34,167 --> 00:09:35,800
I like watching you work.

184
00:09:40,166 --> 00:09:42,351
Make sure you keep that same energy.

185
00:09:44,666 --> 00:09:45,666
I will.

186
00:09:46,066 --> 00:09:48,066
Just let know if you
need me to do anything.

187
00:09:49,933 --> 00:09:50,933
In that case...

188
00:09:51,446 --> 00:09:53,766
Go to the market. I'll write
down a shopping list for you.

189
00:09:56,266 --> 00:09:57,366
Come with me.

190
00:09:57,666 --> 00:09:59,186
I don't even know where the market is.

191
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:00,400
Oh, right.

192
00:10:00,933 --> 00:10:02,693
You've never been to
the market around here.

193
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:03,800
Yeah.

194
00:10:03,966 --> 00:10:04,966
Let's go together then.

195
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:07,900
What should we have for dinner?

196
00:10:10,133 --> 00:10:11,133
Anything.

197
00:10:11,666 --> 00:10:13,566
"Anything" is not on the menu.

198
00:10:14,100 --> 00:10:15,260
What do you want to eat then?

199
00:10:16,300 --> 00:10:17,300
Anything.

200
00:10:17,533 --> 00:10:18,866
Ow, ow, ow!

201
00:10:20,866 --> 00:10:22,806
The "anything" menu...

202
00:10:22,807 --> 00:10:24,035
doesn't exist!

203
00:10:24,036 --> 00:10:27,372
Stop saying that, or
I'll pinch your cheeks.

204
00:10:27,373 --> 00:10:28,505
Ow, ow, ow!

205
00:10:29,373 --> 00:10:30,373
Okay, okay.

206
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:33,080
So, what are we having for dinner tonight?

207
00:10:33,133 --> 00:10:34,666
Cooking or eating out?

208
00:10:36,533 --> 00:10:37,733
Let Erng-Erng cook.

209
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:40,733
I want to eat my lovely wife's cooking.

210
00:10:42,700 --> 00:10:43,800
Omelet it is, then.

211
00:10:45,966 --> 00:10:47,976
We don't even need to go
to the market for an omelet.

212
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,300
There are eggs in the fridge.

213
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:51,066
I wasn't finished yet. Hmm?

214
00:10:51,300 --> 00:10:53,260
You talk back so much, I
should smack those lips.

215
00:10:53,733 --> 00:10:57,466
I was going to say omelet,
squid basil stir-fry, and some soup.

216
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,459
I want pickled mustard greens soup.

217
00:11:03,460 --> 00:11:06,468
But it needs meat
because I don't eat veggies.

218
00:11:06,469 --> 00:11:07,531
But I like the sour broth.

219
00:11:08,810 --> 00:11:09,810
Pork ribs, then?

220
00:11:10,202 --> 00:11:10,793
Do you like that?

221
00:11:10,793 --> 00:11:11,793
I love it.

222
00:11:14,333 --> 00:11:14,900
Hia.

223
00:11:14,966 --> 00:11:15,466
What?

224
00:11:15,666 --> 00:11:16,390
What are you doing?

225
00:11:16,391 --> 00:11:17,871
I want to eat pickled mustard greens.

226
00:11:19,338 --> 00:11:19,838
What?

227
00:11:19,839 --> 00:11:20,942
I'm not pickled mustard greens.

228
00:11:20,966 --> 00:11:21,966
I'm an angel.

229
00:11:22,466 --> 00:11:23,586
Then I want to eat an angel.

230
00:11:28,266 --> 00:11:29,626
You're going to fall. Get up here.

231
00:11:47,766 --> 00:11:49,500
Ow, Erng! That hurts.

232
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:52,900
Do you think I don't know
what you're looking at?

233
00:11:53,066 --> 00:11:55,566
What? I wasn't looking at anything.

234
00:11:55,933 --> 00:11:57,533
I just want some Bua Loy.

235
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:58,600
Are you sure?

236
00:11:58,733 --> 00:11:59,233
Yeah.

237
00:11:59,234 --> 00:12:00,700
Are you sure you weren't looking?

238
00:12:01,133 --> 00:12:02,133
Ow!

239
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:03,333
Let go, Erng.

240
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:04,800
Oh, wow.

241
00:12:05,133 --> 00:12:06,301
Ow, that hurts!

242
00:12:06,302 --> 00:12:06,802
Mm.

243
00:12:07,066 --> 00:12:08,333
My ear is going to rip off.

244
00:12:08,533 --> 00:12:09,533
Mm.

245
00:12:09,816 --> 00:12:11,906
Go grab a cart.

246
00:12:12,466 --> 00:12:13,466
Wow.

247
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:15,400
Are you sulking?

248
00:12:17,466 --> 00:12:18,466
No.

249
00:12:19,766 --> 00:12:21,133
Your voice went totally high.

250
00:12:26,966 --> 00:12:29,533
Bua Loy, my dear friend...

251
00:12:31,466 --> 00:12:33,533
Where is my Bua Loy?

252
00:12:35,666 --> 00:12:36,166
Oh!

253
00:12:36,167 --> 00:12:37,900
Do you want it that badly?

254
00:12:38,666 --> 00:12:40,000
I don't want Bua Loy anymore.

255
00:12:42,766 --> 00:12:44,100
I'll eat you instead.

256
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:47,800
Mmm.

257
00:12:48,100 --> 00:12:49,566
What do you want to eat, Hia?

258
00:12:51,133 --> 00:12:52,200
I want to eat Erng.

259
00:12:54,700 --> 00:12:56,166
Too bad sis.
He wants to eat me.

260
00:12:59,700 --> 00:13:01,400
So I'll buy everything you have.

261
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:03,705
Hia, take the table too.

262
00:13:03,706 --> 00:13:04,206
Huh?

263
00:13:04,466 --> 00:13:05,075
Take it all.

264
00:13:05,075 --> 00:13:05,600
Wait.

265
00:13:05,866 --> 00:13:06,866
Take the coconuts too.

266
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:08,566
Don't even let them do business.

267
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,000
Uh, excuse me.

268
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:13,066
My boyfriend is just joking.

269
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:14,500
Hope your sales go well.

270
00:14:12,502 --> 00:14:14,168
Peekaboo!

271
00:14:15,905 --> 00:14:16,578
What would you like?

272
00:14:16,579 --> 00:14:17,752
This one.

273
00:14:18,300 --> 00:14:19,300
I'll take this.

274
00:14:37,463 --> 00:14:38,498
Look at that fish.

275
00:14:45,396 --> 00:14:46,396
Go ahead.

276
00:14:53,166 --> 00:14:54,166
Go ahead.

277
